  After an epic journey across the breadth of the solar system, NASA’s New Horizons spacecraft is finally nearing its destination: the Pluto system, a staggering 3 billion miles from Earth. In December, after a journey of nine years, the spacecraft was brought out of hibernation for the last time in preparation for its rendezvous with the dwarf planet the week of July 12. The upcoming Pluto flyby, once billed as the ‘first trip to the last planet,’ is actually the first visit to an entirely new class of worlds, says planetary scientist William McKinnon.
